-- Peru Stocks: Credicorp, Rio Alto, Southern Copper Climb
-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 2011-12-23T18:03:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-23/peru-stocks-credicorp-rio-alto-southern-copper-climb.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1 p.m. in Lima.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose 0.2 percent to 19,423.09. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index  gained 0.3 percent to 2,523.58.  Mining companies advanced after copper rose on signs that
U.S. economic growth may spur demand for industrial metals.  Rio Cristal Resources Corp. (RCZ)  , a Canadian
exploration company, climbed 11 percent to 10 cents.  Rio Alto
Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold exploration company, rose
1.3 percent to $3.16.  Southern Copper Corp.  (SCCO PE), Peru’s
biggest copper producer, gained 1.2 percent to $30.90.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-services
company, advanced 0.6 percent to $107.63, a two-week high, after
U.S. stocks rose.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in  Lima  at 
